snippet.textDisplay: For future reference, its best when you don't melt the butter, just soften it so that when you mash it together with the sugar it just gives in easily. Melting the butter just melt some of the sugar contents and gives the cookie dough a very oily finish and you don't want that.  You want a dry cookie. And before you roll the dough, make sure to spread flour on the table and on the dough to make sure it doesn't stick. This is also a reason why you don't melt the butter. Hope 2020 you good vibed ^-^
